t, suggests the beginning of a slow-down in\nthe spread of infections. However, since the rate of slowing down beyond the\nturning point is small, the cumulative number of infections is likely to\nsaturate to about $3.52 \\times 10^5$ around late July, provided the lock-down\nconditions continue to prevail.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Jun 2020 01:27:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 6 Jun 2020 14:17:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-09"}
